metadata.name: Death Valley Moth
metadata.description:
Inspired by Gustave Dore, Beksinksi and the great old movies of Ray Harryhausen this frightening little creature was a joy to draw. Moths have strong connections to the darker side of our world, also, symbolising change, death and rebirth. 

Facing the Fire.

Traditional hand drawing with pen&ink taking over 100 hours in creation, any final purchase over 2 Eth will have the option of the original drawing framed in black & gold.
